@non-Jedi the problem to solve here is to download the keys of a user whenever they join an encrypted room, and track their device list for changes. Those happen very often, and we are notified via a new field in `/sync/`. The whole download process is also quite heavy with a lot of checks. For these reasons, this all has to be done in a non-blocking way. Also, we have to ensure that only one download request is in flight at a time in order to prevent various races from happening.
Hence this PR adds a background thread, which will always be there if encryption is enabled when instantiating `MatrixClient`.  
You may like to comment on the general idea, but I don't think it could have been done any other way (mostly I felt that you should know about this thread and the rationale behind it). What gets added to [client.py](https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-python-sdk/pull/238/files#diff-6770c150117812114aea5a8aab1b7da9) and [room.py](https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-python-sdk/pull/238/files#diff-1e3f0d25ba4b2cf8ef4f9434e7538be0) is pretty minimal and straightforward, since all of the logic is hidden in `device_list.py`.

